Frank CARRARA, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6803. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 12, 1932. Anthony J. Stella, of Tacoma, Wash., for appellant. Anthony Savage, U. S. Atty., and Tom De Wolfe, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Seattle, Wash.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal herein dismissed for failure of .appellant to print and file brief as required by rule 24 of the Rules of Practice of this court
